          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Three different targets and geometries were used",
                " -1) close geometry setup with a target of",
                "     210+-21 ug/cm2 of melamine (C3N6H6) produced by",
                "     evaporation onto Al disks.",
                " -2) A target chamber was used. The target material was",
                "     evaporated on 0.1mm thick Al disks with a",
                "     thickness of 125+-13 ug/cm2. The target was at",
                "     2mm from the the Li7 target and exposed to the",
                "     full neutron cone.",
                " -3) A Si detector was the central layer of a chamber,",
                "     which the downstream part was filled with argon Ga",
                "     and the upstream part with air (78.02% N2,",
                "     20.95% O2,0.93% Ar), both parts at",
                "     atmospheric pressure. The nitrogen air target is a",
                "     cylinder defined by the active area of the",
                "     detector and an Al plug."
              ]
            }
          ],
